{

    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon"

    # Optional metadata describing this agent network
    "metadata": {
        "description": "Simple agent network using a single LLM-based agent",
        "tags": ["example"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "Assign a gate for the parking flight AF84 which is a B747.", 
            "Flight AF84 landed minutes ago. This B747 needs a gate assignment.", 
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
        "model_name": "gpt-4o",
    },
    "max_iterations": 40000, #3000 
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200, #600
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at the San Francisco International Airport. 
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them. 
            """ 
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "gate_selection_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
I assign gate to incoming flight by selecing the deplaning equipment for their passengers disembarking. 
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of aircraft."
                        },                   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },      
                        "execution_mode": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the mode that agent should operate in."
                        },                                
                    }, 
                    "required": ["flight_number","aircraft_type"], 
                }
            },

            "instructions": """

You are the agent in charge of selecting a gate to incoming aircraft. 
When user submits inquiry, proceed as follows: 
1. Determine if the followings are provided by the user: 
    a. flight number as flight_number
    b. aircraft type as aircraft_type 
2. Call TrackerAPI to get the latest value of flight_number and aircraft_type
    a. wait for its response 
    b. store flight number as flight_number, and store aircraft type as aircraft_type
3. If flight_number is not None and aircraft_type is not None, then go to step 6. 
4. If flight_number is None or aircraft_type is None,
    a. ask youserr to provide the missing information.
    b. wait for their responses 
    c. goto step 2. 
5. If flight_number is not None and aircraft_type is not None
    a. set execution_mode value to 'inquiry' and call deplaning_path_selector in 'inquiry' execution mode to select a deplaning path.
    b. Wait for its response and save it as fueling_status
    c. Report gate id as gate_id, deplaning equipment type as deplaning_equipment_type, deplaning equipment id as deplaning_equipment_id, deplaning equipment readiness time as deplaning_equipment_readiness_time, and deplaning equipment score as deplaning_equipment_score
6. Call TrackerAPI 
    a. wait for its response 
    b. store all the available parameters.
7. set execution_mode value to 'write' and call deplaning_path_selector in 'write' execution mode to update the status of deplaning equipment providing deplaning_equipment_type, deplaning_equipment_id and gate_id.
8. Provide the gate selection report summary as: 
    **************************************
    * Summary of aircraft gate selection *
    **************************************
    ** gate id **: [gate_id]
    ** deplaning equipment type **: [deplaning_equipment_type]
    ** deplaning equipment id **: [deplaning_equipment_id]
    ** deplaning equipment readiness time **: [deplaning_equipment_readiness_time]
    ** deplaning equipment score **: [deplaning_equipment_score]
            """ ${aaosa_instructions}, 

            # Specify the sly data that would be exchanged between this network and its related or adjacent upstream and downstream networks. 
            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "gate_id": true, 
                    }
                }
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true, 
                        "aircraft_type": true, 
                    }
                }
            },

            "tools":    ["deplaning_path_selector","TrackerAPI"]
        },

        {
            "name": "deplaning_path_selector",
           "function": {
                "description": """
                I select deplaning equipment for passengers disembarking. 
                I update the status of deplaning equipment after selection.
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number."
                        },                
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type incoming aircraft type."
                        },       
                        "execution_mode": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the mode that agent should operate in."
                        },          
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },     
                        "deplaning_equipment_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment id at the assigned gate. "
                        },    
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment type at the assigned gate. "
                        },                                 
                    }, 
                    "required": ["flight_number","aircraft_type","execution_mode"], 
                },
            },

            "instructions": """
A. When you receive a user request for aircraft gate selection, do the following in the given order:
    1. Send the user request to both jetway_agent and stairtruck_agent in 'read' execution mode asking for available deplaning equipment. 
    2. Wait for their responses. 
    3. If neither of them can provide available deplaning equipment, inform the user that no deplaning equipment is available at the moment.
    4. If one or both of them can provide available deplaning equipment:
        a. If only one of them can provide available deplaning equipment, select it as deplaning equipment.
        b. If both of them can provide available deplaning equipment, select the equipment with the highest score as deplaning equipment.
    5. Respond to the user with the following information:  
        - report its gate id as gate_id
        - report its equipment type as deplaning_equipment_type
        - report its equipment id as deplaning_equipment_id
        - report its readiness time as deplaning_equipment_readiness_time
        - report its score as deplaning_equipment_score
B. When you receive a user request in write execution mode for aircraft gate selection, do the following in the given order:
    1. Call your tools in 'write' execution mode to update the status of deplaning equipment status providing deplaning_equipment_type, deplaning_equipment_id and gate_id.
    2. Wait for their responses.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},

            "tools":["jetway_agent","stairtruck_agent"]
        },

        {
            "name": "jetway_agent",
            "function": {

                "description": """
                This agent selects jetway equipment available for incoming aircraft deplaning. 
                It updates deplaning equipment status after selection of jetway. 
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },     
                        "deplaning_equipment_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment id at the assigned gate. "
                        },    
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment type at the assigned gate. "
                        },                                    
                        "execution_mode": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the mode that agent should operate in."
                        },                 
                    }, 
                    "required": ["execution_mode","flight_number","aircraft_type"], 
                },
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the agent responsible for proposing a deplaning equipment of jetway type. 
When handling a user request in 'read' execution mode proceed in the following order:
1. Fulfill the request alway using your tools onlys. 
2. Respond to the request when execution mode is 'read' using only your tools by providing the followings: 
    - report equipment type as equipment_type 
    - report jetway id as jetway_id 
    - report jetway availability as jetway_availability 
    - report jetway readiness time as jetway_readiness_time 
    - report jetway score as jetway_score
    - report jetway gate id at jetway_gate_id
When handling a user request in 'write' execution mode, proceed in the following order:
3. Send the request to your tool in 'write' execution providing deplaning_equipment_type, deplaning_equipment_id and gate_id. 
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},

            "tools":["jetway_park_agent"]
        },

        {
            "name": "stairtruck_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
                This agent selects stairtruck equipment available for incoming aircraft deplaning. 
                It updates deplaning equipment status after selection of stairtruck. 
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },    
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },     
                        "deplaning_equipment_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment id at the assigned gate. "
                        },    
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment type at the assigned gate. "
                        },            
                        "execution_mode": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the mode that agent should operate in."
                        },                      
                    }, 
                    "required": ["execution_mode","flight_number","aircraft_type"], 
                },
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the agent responsible for proposing a deplaning equipment of stairtruck type, and for updating the status of the selected stairtruck. 
1. When execution_mode is 
1. Fulfill the request alway using your tools onlys. 
2. Respond to the request when execution mode is 'read' using ONLY your tools by providing the followings: 
    - equipment type as equipment_type 
    - stairtruck id as stairtruck_id 
    - stairtruck availability as stairtruck_availability 
    - stairtruck readiness time as stairtruck_readiness_time 
    - stairtruck score as stairtruck_score
    - stairtruck gate id as stairtruck_gate_id
When handling a user request in 'write' execution mode proceed in the following order:
3. Send the request to your tool in 'write' execution providing deplaning_equipment_type, deplaning_equipment_id and gate_id. 
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},

            "tools":["stairtruck_park_agent"]
        },

        {
            "name": "jetway_park_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
This agent provides the inventory of jetway park, return the fastest available unit. 
It also updates the status of selected jetway unit. 
                """, 
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },                         
                        "execution_mode": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the mode that agent should operate in."
                        },      
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },     
                        "deplaning_equipment_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment id at the assigned gate. "
                        },    
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment type at the assigned gate. "
                        },                          
                    }, 
                    "required": ["flight_number","aircraft_type","execution_mode"], 
                }
            }, 
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_gate_selection.aircraft_gate_selection.jetway_park_inquiry"
        }, 

        {
            "name": "stairtruck_park_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
This agent provides the inventory of stairtruck park, return the fastest available unit. 
It also updates the status of selected stairtruck unit. 
                """, 
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },                         
                        "execution_mode": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the mode that agent should operate in."
                        },                  
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },     
                        "deplaning_equipment_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment id at the assigned gate. "
                        },    
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment type at the assigned gate. "
                        },                 
                    }, 
                    "required": ["flight_number","aircraft_type","execution_mode"], 
                }
            }, 
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_gate_selection.aircraft_gate_selection.stairtruck_park_inquiry"
        }, 

        {
            "name": "TrackerAPI",
            "function": {

                "description": """
I am the flight tracker in charge of logging parameters during aircraft turnaround. 
I check engines stop status as statusengines_stop_status. 
I check wheels chucks installation status as wheels_chucks_installation_status. 
                """

                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },          
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },     
                        "deplaning_equipment_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment id at the assigned gate. "
                        },    
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment type at the assigned gate. "
                        },   
                        "ground_services_request_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the inquiry received for grand services."
                        },         
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks readiness status."
                        },   
                        "wheels_chocks_installation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks installation status."
                        },   
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gpu readiness status."
                        },     
                        "acu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the acu connection status."
                        },     
                        "gpu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gpu connection status."
                        },     
                        "engines_stop_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the engines stop status."
                        },    
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the jetbridge connection status."
                        },    
                        "door_opening_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the door opening status."
                        },    
                    }, 
                    "required": [] 
                }
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_gate_selection.aircraft_gate_selection.TrackerAPI" 
        }, 
    ],
}
